.TH "i2c_handle_smbus_alert" 9 "i2c_handle_smbus_alert" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i2c_handle_smbus_alert \- Handle an SMBus alert
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i2c_handle_smbus_alert
.BI "(struct i2c_client *ara "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ara" 12
the ARA client on the relevant adapter
.SH "CONTEXT"
can't sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Helper function to be called from an I2C bus driver's interrupt
handler. It will schedule the alert work, in turn calling the
corresponding I2C device driver's alert function.

It is assumed that ara is a valid i2c client previously returned by
\fBi2c_new_smbus_alert_device\fP.
